## WeatherService (`weather_service.dart`)

### Purpose
Handle weather-related operations (mock for now).

### Responsibilities
- Get current weather
- Get forecast
- Weather condition mapping
- Temperature conversion

### Pattern
```dart
class WeatherService {
  static final WeatherService _instance = WeatherService._internal();
  factory WeatherService() => _instance;
  WeatherService._internal();
  
  // Mock weather data
  Future<WeatherData> getWeather(String location) async {
    // Simulate API delay
    await Future.delayed(Duration(milliseconds: 500));
    
    return WeatherData(
      temperature: 22.0,
      condition: WeatherCondition.sunny,
      humidity: 65,
      windSpeed: 12.5,
    );
  }
  
  String getWeatherIcon(WeatherCondition condition) {
    switch (condition) {
      case WeatherCondition.sunny:
        return '☀️';
      case WeatherCondition.cloudy:
        return '☁️';
      case WeatherCondition.rainy:
        return '🌧️';
      case WeatherCondition.snowy:
        return '❄️';
    }
  }
  
  String getStatusMessage(WeatherData weather) {
    if (weather.temperature > 30) {
      return 'Very hot - bring extra water';
    } else if (weather.temperature < 5) {
      return 'Cold - check sleeping bag rating';
    } else if (weather.condition == WeatherCondition.rainy) {
      return 'Rain expected - pack waterproof gear';
    }
    return 'Good to go';
  }
}

class WeatherData {
  final double temperature;
  final WeatherCondition condition;
  final int humidity;
  final double windSpeed;
  
  WeatherData({
    required this.temperature,
    required this.condition,
    required this.humidity,
    required this.windSpeed,
  });
}

enum WeatherCondition { sunny, cloudy, rainy, snowy }
```

